==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin [[alcaicus]], from Greek [[αλκαικος]], from [[Αλκαιος]] ‘Alcaeus’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /æl'keɪɪk/

===Adjective===
'''alcaic'''
# pertaining to [[w:Alcaeus|Alcaeus]], a Greek lyric poet of around 600BC; especially, of a verse meter in a four-line stanza which he supposedly invented

===Noun===
'''alcaic'''
# ''(in plural)'' alcaic verses

